raw_data.title: IT/Network Specialist
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibilities: Maintains a reliable, secure, and efficient data communications network. Capability to deploy, configure, maintain, and monitor all active network equipment in order to ensure smooth network operation. Duties: 1. Fully supports, configures, maintains, and upgrades customer’s networks and in-house servers. 2. Installs and integrates new server hardware and applications. 3. Monitors relevant sources for potentially critical updates. 4. Provides hands-on experience pertaining to networking, routing, and switching. 5. Excellent knowledge of best practices around management, control, and monitoring of server infrastructure. 6. Provides technical experience with firewalls, Internet VPN’s remote implementation, troubleshooting, and problem resolution. 7. Ability to set up and configure server hardware. 8. Understands backup and recovery software and methodologies. 9. Great at organizing, prioritizing, and multitasking. Minimum Education: Bachelor’s degree Minimum Experience: 4 years

raw_data.title: Graphic Designer 1, Project Manager/Art Director**
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibilities: Expert knowledge and ability of Graphic Design, Art Direction and Project Management, capability to provide technical writing to clients. Provides general project supervision, designs, and/or coordinates the development and design of a wide range of electronic and/or printed graphic materials, involving a variety of integrated steps and processes including technical writing, and requiring extensive expert knowledge of specialized, multi-faceted design concepts and media. Creates complex, original graphic design and comprehensive layout concepts, and oversees and coordinates production of materials. Leads and guides the work of other graphic designers as art Director and/or Project Manager. Duties: 1. Conceptualizes, plans, designs, and produces a wide range of specialized graphic and/or illustrative material, to include multimedia concepts, as appropriate. 2. Work with clientele to ascertain needs and to develop graphic directions, concepts, and specifications for assigned projects. 3. Plans production schedules for the various steps in the design process, analyzes and projects development costs, and develops project budgets and workflow. 4. Identifies, selects, and coordinates vendors for printing and publication services, as appropriate to the project; may write and process requests for proposals for printing requisitions; identifies and recommends contractors, such as typesetters, printers, illustrators, photographers, and/or cartographers. 5. Oversees and coordinates the production process; develops and writes printing and/or other production specifications, and selects appropriate production media and materials, such as ink and paper; inspects proofs for accuracy and adherence to appropriate production standards. 6. Provides technical advice and guidance, and serves as liaison with production personnel, authors, publishers, clients, and/or printing representatives on design and technical graphics issues. 7. Participates in production and/or marketing planning group sessions and meetings, on a project basis. 8. Writes and edits basic copy, as appropriate, which may include press releases in some instances. 9. May coordinate a graphics or photographic library and/or maintain digital records. 10. May provide technical computer support and install software programs. 11. May create and produce animated videos and animated portions of live videos using computers and video production equipment. 12. May supervise and/or lead lower graded staff and/or student employees. 13. Performs miscellaneous job-related duties as assigned. Minimum Education: Bachelor’s degree Minimum Experience: 4 years
raw_data.key_words: graphic design,technical writing,conceptual design,technical advice,editing material

raw_data.title: Proof Reading Specialist**
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibilities: The proofreader is responsible for assuring that the text of any product that involves writing is free of any errors. In addition, they implement corrections that enhance readers’ engagement and accessibility with the materials. Duties: 1. Reviews and edits documents for accurate use of grammar and content. 2. When copy-editing, evaluates the work to address any potential issues with style and tone 3. Reports to project supervisor or manager. 4. Works independently within established procedures associated with the specific job function. Minimum Education: Associates degree Minimum Experience: 1 year

raw_data.title: Web Specialist**
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibilities: Web specialists are responsible for creating, designing, and maintaining websites for businesses, individuals, or organizations. They offer a wide range of services, including designing, editing, proofing, site maintenance, installing website updates, and fixing bugs. They often use content management software to perform their duties. Web specialists must be able to effectively communicate the business's brand through the company's web site. They have website design and management experience, as well as some computer programming and information technology knowledge. Duties: 1. Provides effective and functional web designs to company that met their specific business/personal needs. 2. Works directly with client to establish project scope, interaction guidelines, and project timelines. 3. Ensures the accuracy of website content by thoroughly editing and cross-checking materials. 4. Increases clients’ online presence through one-on-one individual collaboration. 5. Manages clients’ website designs from concept to final product. 6. Assists the internet marketing team in updated client websites and increasing search engine exposure. 7. Collaborates with the project manager, as well as programmers, to maximize the functionality of clients’ website layout. 8. Assists the IT manager in setting up customers’ web site hosting on company servers, registering domain names, and preparing email accounts. 9. Provides technical guidance for developing and implementing website designs that enhance clients’ online presence. 10. Coordinates with clients to plan web development projects from concept through completion, utilizing a variety of web development tools and technology. Minimum Education: Associates degree Minimum Experience: 1 year

raw_data.title: 508 Compliance technician 1**
raw_data.description: Functional Responsibilities: Expert knowledge of Graphic Design and publications layout. The 508 Document Compliance Technician 1 will create and edit complex and simple documents to insure accessibility to people with disabilities in compliance with Section 508 requirements and standards. The specialist will convert and format documents to be readable by assistive technology devices following Federal and departmental policies. The technician 1 will continuously review procedures and provide recommendations for improving compliance. Thus, they will recommend and implement a system of workflow to insure compliance is part of the document/publication development process. Duties: 1. Intermediate skills with Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Adobe InDesign, and CS5 or better. 2. Attention to detail and organization skills. 3. Advanced knowledge with Windows 10 Professional or better. 4. Experience working with screen readers and other assistive technology and related software tools. 5. Work with clientele to recommend graphic directions and concepts for assigned projects. 6. Prioritize/direct the production process to complete each project within the timeframe required. 7. Selects appropriate production media and materials to meet production standards. 8. May organize and participate in production and/or planning group sessions and meetings, on an individual project basis. 9. Creates Charts, graphs, illustrations tables and word charts, as appropriate. 10. Install software programs. 11. Interface with lower graded staff and employees. 12. Performs miscellaneous job-related duties as assigned. Minimum Education: Associates degree Minimum Experience: 2 years
